genresAdvancedInfo.name: scottish gaelic folk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Scottish Gaelic Folk music is a sub-genre of Scottish Folk music that focuses on the traditional songs and tunes sung in the Scottish Gaelic language. The music is characterized by its haunting melodies and the use of instruments such as the harp, tin whistle, and bodhrán. The lyrics often tell stories of Scottish mythology, folklore, and the beauty of the Scottish landscape.
